id: pm-8r2r
title: pm files --add bare path fails with misleading error (scope implied required)
description: Agents passing pm files <id> --add 'src/file.ts' get error 'Expected key=value entries'. The error does not mention that the correct format is path=src/file.ts or that scope defaults to project. Misleads agents into thinking scope is required. Fixed by adding path-context hint to buildOptionSpecificKvGuidance in parse.ts.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agents,error-message,files,ux
created_at: "2026-05-01T18:58:40.497Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-01T19:29:07.543Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-3fti
severity: medium
resolution: "Added path-detection heuristic in buildOptionSpecificKvGuidance: when raw value looks like a file path and optionName is --add, the error now includes 'path=<file-path>[,scope=project|global]. The scope field is optional and defaults to project'."
expected_result: "Expected closure outcome: Fixed: buildOptionSpecificKvGuidance in parse.ts now detects file-path-like values for --add and emits format hint. Verified working."
actual_result: "Actual closure outcome: Fixed: buildOptionSpecificKvGuidance in parse.ts now detects file-path-like values for --add and emits format hint. Verified working."
close_reason: "Fixed: buildOptionSpecificKvGuidance in parse.ts now detects file-path-like values for --add and emits format hint. Verified working."
body: ""
